App-Prove-Plugin-TraceUse version 1.0.2

This plugin to prove aims to keep track of any non-core modules
invoked during testing and report those for easy entry into
dependency lists in Makefile.PL and Build.PL.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

Alternatively, to install with Module::Build, you can use the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install


DEPENDENCIES

App::Prove
Test::Perl::Critic
Test::Pod::Coverage
Test::Most
Set::Object
Test::Pod
File::Slurp
Tree::Simple


